Being a woman founder is difficult, especially when it comes to funding. Less than 2% of venture capital went to women entrepreneurs last year, and experts believe the Silicon Valley Bank collapse will continue to affect the underserved founders who relied on them. "It's put more emphasis on the imbalance of how we put out capital in this country," @toryburchfoundation President Laurie Fabiano told @techcrunch in an interview about our new Funding Finder tool. By giving founders more information about what financing options exist and which may suit their businesses, we can help more grow and scale.

Tap the link in our bio to learn how we hope to impact the funding landscape for small business owners.

In our Resort 2024 collection, a dichotomy plays out between clean lines and intense texture. Balletic tulle creates movement and soft volume around the body, balanced by streamlined coats, tops and skirts. Stretch cotton and satin are transformed through fabric manipulation: Chalky paint gives structure to an embroidered muslin dress; a coat that appears to be supple leather is actually glazed viscose; metal studs mimic reptilian scales; and a patent jacket is laser- cut to feathery effect. #ToryBurchResort24 #ToryBurch

The cat and rabbit prints in our Resort 2024 collection are by German photographer Walter Schels, known for capturing animals in heroic, almost-human portraits. For handbags and shoes, we reimagined our signatures. The Swing bag is scaled down to a miniature size; the Ballet Loafer now comes in our T Monogram jacquard; and the Lee Radziwill Double Bag features a fluffy cow print. #ToryBurchResort24 #ToryBurch #WalterSchels
